verses.text_plain: This is the book of the generations of Adam. In the day that God created man, in the likeness of God made he him;
verses.verse_html: 1This is the book of the generations of Adam. In the day that God created man, in the likeness of God made he him;

verses.text_plain: Male and female created he them; and blessed them, and called their name Adam, in the day when they were created.
verses.verse_html: 2Male and female created he them; and blessed them, and called their name Adam, in the day when they were created.

verses.text_plain: And Adam lived an hundred and thirty years, and begat a son in his own likeness, after his image; and called his name Seth:
verses.verse_html: 3And Adam lived an hundred and thirty years, and begat a son in his own likeness, after his image; and called his name Seth:

verses.text_plain: And the days of Adam after he had begotten Seth were eight hundred years: and he begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 4And the days of Adam after he had begotten Seth were eight hundred years: and he begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 5And all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Seth lived an hundred and five years, and begat Enos:
verses.verse_html:
6And Seth lived an hundred and five years, and begat Enos: ▼
▼ Enos: Heb. Enosh

verses.text_plain: And Seth lived after he begat Enos eight hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 7And Seth lived after he begat Enos eight hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 8And all the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Enos lived ninety years, and begat Cainan:
verses.verse_html:
9And Enos lived ninety years, and begat Cainan: ▼
▼ Cainan: Heb. Kenan

verses.text_plain: And Enos lived after he begat Cainan eight hundred and fifteen years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 10And Enos lived after he begat Cainan eight hundred and fifteen years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Enos were nine hundred and five years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 11And all the days of Enos were nine hundred and five years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Cainan lived seventy years, and begat Mahalaleel:
verses.verse_html:
12And Cainan lived seventy years, and begat Mahalaleel: ▼
▼ Mahalaleel: Gr. Maleleel

verses.text_plain: And Cainan lived after he begat Mahalaleel eight hundred and forty years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 13And Cainan lived after he begat Mahalaleel eight hundred and forty years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Cainan were nine hundred and ten years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 14And all the days of Cainan were nine hundred and ten years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Mahalaleel lived sixty and five years, and begat Jared:
verses.verse_html:
15And Mahalaleel lived sixty and five years, and begat Jared: ▼
▼ Jared: Heb. Jered

verses.text_plain: And Mahalaleel lived after he begat Jared eight hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 16And Mahalaleel lived after he begat Jared eight hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Mahalaleel were eight hundred ninety and five years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 17And all the days of Mahalaleel were eight hundred ninety and five years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Jared lived an hundred sixty and two years, and he begat Enoch:
verses.verse_html: 18And Jared lived an hundred sixty and two years, and he begat Enoch:

verses.text_plain: And Jared lived after he begat Enoch eight hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 19And Jared lived after he begat Enoch eight hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Jared were nine hundred sixty and two years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 20And all the days of Jared were nine hundred sixty and two years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Enoch lived sixty and five years, and begat Methuselah:
verses.verse_html:
21And Enoch lived sixty and five years, and begat Methuselah: ▼
▼ Methuselah: Gr. Mathusala

verses.text_plain: And Enoch walked with God after he begat Methuselah three hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 22And Enoch walked with God after he begat Methuselah three hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Enoch were three hundred sixty and five years:
verses.verse_html: 23And all the days of Enoch were three hundred sixty and five years:

verses.text_plain: And Enoch walked with God: and he was not; for God took him.
verses.verse_html: 24And Enoch walked with God: and he was not; for God took him.

verses.text_plain: And Methuselah lived an hundred eighty and seven years, and begat Lamech:
verses.verse_html: 25And Methuselah lived an hundred eighty and seven years, and begat Lamech:

verses.text_plain: And Methuselah lived after he begat Lamech seven hundred eighty and two years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html:
26And Methuselah lived after he begat Lamech seven hundred eighty and two years, and begat sons and daughters: ▼
▼ Lamech: Heb. Lemech

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred sixty and nine years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 27And all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred sixty and nine years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Lamech lived an hundred eighty and two years, and begat a son:
verses.verse_html: 28And Lamech lived an hundred eighty and two years, and begat a son:

verses.text_plain: And he called his name Noah, saying, This same shall comfort us concerning our work and toil of our hands, because of the ground which the Lord hath cursed.
verses.verse_html:
29And he called his name Noah, saying, This same shall comfort us concerning our work and toil of our hands, because of the ground which the Lord hath cursed. ▼
▼ Noah: Gr. Noe: that is Rest, or, Comfort

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Noah: Gr. Noe: that is Rest, or, Comfort
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Noah: Gr. Noe: that is Rest, or, Comfort

verses.text_plain: And Lamech lived after he begat Noah five hundred ninety and five years, and begat sons and daughters:
verses.verse_html: 30And Lamech lived after he begat Noah five hundred ninety and five years, and begat sons and daughters:

verses.text_plain: And all the days of Lamech were seven hundred seventy and seven years: and he died.
verses.verse_html: 31And all the days of Lamech were seven hundred seventy and seven years: and he died.

verses.text_plain: And Noah was five hundred years old: and Noah begat Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
verses.verse_html: 32And Noah was five hundred years old: and Noah begat Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
